
test_hkdf: User container for performing HKDF functions

Usage:
    hkdf-extract [core] [salt bytes] [ikm bytes]
    hkdf-expand [core] [pkr bytes] [info bytes] [length]
    hkdf-ext-exp [core] [salt bytes] [ikm bytes] [info bytes] [length]
Note: Set %00 or 0 for NULL parameter

Load the user container and see usage in logs:
$ mwtest.py -c100 run test_hkdf.img
$ cmtest log

Generate a pseudorandom key of 32 bytes with SHA-256:
cmtest cmd hkdf-extract s2hc %00 %0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b -f100
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 32 bytes OK
00000000: 19 ef 24 a3 2c 71 7b 16  7f 33 a9 1d 6f 64 8b df  |..$.,q{..3..od..|
00000010: 96 59 67 76 af db 63 77  ac 43 4c 1c 29 3c cb 04  |.Ygv..cw.CL.)<..|

Derive a cryptographic key of a specified length with SHA-256:
cmtest cmd hkdf-expand s2hc %19ef24a32c717b167f33a91d6f648bdf96596776afdb6377ac434c1c293ccb04
%00 42 -f100
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 42 bytes OK
00000000: 8d a4 e7 75 a5 63 c1 8f  71 5f 80 2a 06 3c 5a 31  |...u.c..q_.*.<Z1|
00000010: b8 a1 1f 5c 5e e1 87 9e  c3 45 4e 5f 3c 73 8d 2d  |...\^....EN_<s.-|
00000020: 9d 20 13 95 fa a4 b6 1a  96 c8                    |. ........|

Generate a pseudorandom key and derive a cryptographic key of a specified length:
cmtest cmd hkdf-ext-exp s2hc %00 %0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b0b %00 42 -f100
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 42 bytes OK
00000000: 8d a4 e7 75 a5 63 c1 8f  71 5f 80 2a 06 3c 5a 31  |...u.c..q_.*.<Z1|
00000010: b8 a1 1f 5c 5e e1 87 9e  c3 45 4e 5f 3c 73 8d 2d  |...\^....EN_<s.-|
00000020: 9d 20 13 95 fa a4 b6 1a  96 c8                    |. ........|

Unload the user container:
$ mwtest.py -c100 unload
